            <h1 class="white-text"> A Short Background 🌿</h1>
            <p class="justify white-text"> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; On a Sunday afternoon back in 2005, both young and new 
            parents, Mark and Liza, were taken by surprise as they had to rush to the nearest emergency 
            hospital - the reason? I was about to be born. After hours of painful labor that my mother had 
            to endure, I finally opened my naive little eyes and cried as loud as I can when I realized that 
            I was born into a bittersweet world full of possibilities yet at the same time &hyphen; <b>full of cruelty</b>. 
            My parents, like any other parent, aspired to create a good life for our family, which required 
            them to work abroad as <i>Overseas Filipino Workers</i> (OFWs). However, both of them had 
            decided to part ways before I even reached my adolescence. Due to this, I grew up without 
            having my parents by my side, and I was left in the care of my sweet grandmother and my 
            loving aunt, and ever since, I grew up in an environment full of strong and independent 
            women who provided me with the right amount of support, care, and love. But life has not 
            been really kind to my younger self, as every bit of little innocence left in my younger version&apos;s 
            body was forcefully stripped out by guiltless people who took advantage of my youth and 
            naivety. These experiences had lasting effects on myself which I am still actively trying to 
            heal from until now. But I believe that all of these experiences also made me who I am, as 
            they taught me a lot of lessons that made me stronger and more resilient now that I am older. 
            With that being said, <b>I may seem to be a reserved and quiet individual, but it just 
            usually takes some time for me to truly warm up to people.</b> <br><br>
            </p>

        
